      "data": {
        "tag": "Structure",
        "title": "Why Graph Structure Matters",
        "body": "Most systems hide relationships. Twilite exposes them directly. Ideas are not isolated. They exist in relation to causes, dependencies, references, abstractions, examples, systems, workflows, and people. A graph preserves those relationships instead of flattening them into linear documents.",
